    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain not-assessed as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. The grid convergence study (documented in the discretization error factor and referenced throughout validation narratives) provides bounding evidence for discretization contribution to hemolysis prediction uncertainty. Despite widespread shortfalls relative to required levels, the overall package is accepted for submission to the regulatory record as a complete documentation of current model credibility state, with all gaps explicitly acknowledged. The systematic grid convergence study is cited as a key completed activity supporting the discretization error factor assessment.",
